      "content": "that makes sense, but i'm trying to get a better feel for the reality of it. i've heard some people say that these hikes are basically a death sentence for local shops in small towns, while others say it's just a necessary step for fairness. from a business consultancy perspective, which side actually holds more weight when you look at the actual data for low-cost areas?",
